notes: Umpire RA Emerson makes his debut in an international match.
25th anniversary of One-day Internationals (first one held on the 5th of January 1971, Australia defeating England at the MCG).
Play started 35 minutes after the scheduled starting time of 1:30pm. Tea interval reduced to 30 minutes, and play extended beyond it's normal finishing time. Match remains at 50 overs per side.
Walsh (apparent thigh strain) substituted from the 11th over to the 17th over.
Browne takes 5 catches and equals the world record for most dismissals by a wicket keeper.
Murali's first over had 3 no-balls for throwing.
Murali's second over had 2 no-balls for throwing.

milestones.description: Browne has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (5) in ODIs for WI, going past Deryck Murray's 4
